WEBVTT

00:03.046 --> 00:05.266
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

00:05.309 --> 00:07.920
Man: Angels, this is unit 51.
We've got a young boy coming in

00:07.964 --> 00:09.444
with a possible
caustic ingestion.

00:09.487 --> 00:12.186
He's having difficulty
breathing. ETA two minutes.

00:12.229 --> 00:13.361
[ Vehicle doors close ]

00:13.404 --> 00:15.058
Oh, my God. Please, help!

00:15.102 --> 00:17.017
Leanne: Don't worry, sweetheart.
We got him. We got him.

00:17.060 --> 00:19.280
-What do you got?
-Doug Kessler, 8 years old,

00:19.323 --> 00:21.195
sister found him
in severe respiratory distress

00:21.238 --> 00:23.327
after ingesting boiling water
through a straw.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.634
Why would he do that?He said he saw it on
the Internet or something.

00:25.677 --> 00:28.941
He's choking on
his own secretions.We need to intubate,

00:28.985 --> 00:30.943
and we need to get him
to center stage now.

00:30.987 --> 00:32.597
Hey, we got him.

00:32.641 --> 00:35.122
What do you see, Dr. Avila?
Talk to me.

00:35.165 --> 00:36.993
I-I don't know.
There's too much swelling.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.604
-Okay, well, keep trying.
-What do we got?

00:39.648 --> 00:41.780
We got severe thermal damage
on the esophagus.

00:41.824 --> 00:43.260
Let me see the X-ray.

00:43.304 --> 00:45.219
-How's that intubation going?
-Oh, I'm almost there.

00:45.262 --> 00:47.177
Oxygen sat down 75%.

00:47.221 --> 00:49.136
I'm almost there.
Give me a second, all right?

00:49.179 --> 00:50.398
He doesn't have a second.
Move.

00:50.441 --> 00:51.312
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

00:51.355 --> 00:53.357
Here we go.

00:53.401 --> 00:56.621
Pneumomediastinum.
He ruptured his esophagus.

00:56.665 --> 00:59.015
He needs the OR now.
Where are the parents?

00:59.059 --> 01:01.974
-They are not here yet.
-Let's go.

01:02.018 --> 01:04.194
Move, move, move,
move, move, move.

01:04.238 --> 01:06.849
♪♪

01:06.892 --> 01:08.416
Mother's phone goes
straight to voicemail.

01:08.459 --> 01:10.157
I left a few messages
at her office.

01:10.200 --> 01:13.029
-I'll keep trying.
-Where are they taking him?

01:13.073 --> 01:16.163
To the OR. Your brother needs
surgery to repair his throat.

01:16.206 --> 01:17.773
Will they be able to fix it?

01:17.816 --> 01:20.254
I'm staying positive,

01:20.297 --> 01:23.039
and I want you
to stay positive, too, okay?

01:23.083 --> 01:25.433
-Okay. [ Crying ]
-Oh, honey. Come here.

01:25.476 --> 01:29.001
-[ Sniffling ]
-[ Whispers ] It's okay.

01:29.045 --> 01:30.742
♪♪

01:30.786 --> 01:33.223
Hey, Savetti, this is
three days in a row

01:33.267 --> 01:36.096
you've been on the rig with us.
What gives?

01:36.139 --> 01:37.358
I gotta have a reason
to do my job?

01:37.401 --> 01:39.186
I'm just saying it's been
a minute

01:39.229 --> 01:40.491
since you've been
on a ridealong.

01:44.060 --> 01:47.716
Will you say something
hopeful? Anything.

01:47.759 --> 01:48.978
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:49.021 --> 01:53.287
Purest Tahitian blue,
bright as Egyptian tan,

01:53.330 --> 01:56.377
cured by a woman's hue.
-Willis.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.292
Aside from the soul of man.

01:58.335 --> 01:59.902
What are you lookin' at?

02:03.384 --> 02:06.126
He got a Realtor. My dad.

02:06.169 --> 02:08.998
For my brother's house.

02:09.041 --> 02:11.566
-You gonna sell?
-No.

02:11.609 --> 02:16.048
It's all he wanted,
was a home.

02:16.092 --> 02:17.485
Would've wanted me
to finish it.

02:17.528 --> 02:18.921
Then that's what
you should do.

02:18.964 --> 02:20.662
Man on radio:
Squad 15, squad 15.

02:20.705 --> 02:22.229
Two boat crash
at Beaman's Wharf in San Pedro.

02:22.272 --> 02:24.448
Multiple injuries.

02:24.492 --> 02:27.495
[ Static crackles ]I hate boats.

02:27.538 --> 02:31.368
[ Touchscreen clicking ]

02:31.412 --> 02:32.282
[ Whooshes ]

02:32.326 --> 02:37.374
[ Clicking continues ]

02:37.418 --> 02:39.768
[ Whoosh ]

02:39.811 --> 02:43.337
[ Clicking continues ]

02:43.380 --> 02:45.513
[ Whoosh ]

02:45.556 --> 02:54.348
♪♪

02:54.391 --> 02:55.914
Hi.

02:55.958 --> 02:58.526
Hi.

02:58.569 --> 03:04.401
♪♪

03:04.445 --> 03:06.186
Um, I have to go to work.

03:07.665 --> 03:10.364
Okay...[ Door opens ]

03:10.407 --> 03:12.496
[ Door closes ]

03:13.541 --> 03:15.412
[ Siren wailing ]

03:15.456 --> 03:20.243
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:20.287 --> 03:21.418
All right, let's go.

03:21.462 --> 03:23.420
All right, I'll take
the walking wounded.

03:23.464 --> 03:24.813
You take the trawler.

03:24.856 --> 03:27.163
-Which one's the trawler?
-The one on fire.

03:27.207 --> 03:28.556
[ Groans ]

03:28.599 --> 03:30.427
-[ Grunts ]
-All right. Hey, hey, hey.

03:30.471 --> 03:33.038
My dad -- he needs help. He's on
the charter. He's pinned.

03:33.082 --> 03:35.519
The trawler came in too fast.
You gotta help him!I got it.

03:35.563 --> 03:39.436
[ Sirens wailing ]

03:39.480 --> 03:41.351
[ Horns honk ]

03:41.395 --> 03:43.440
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

03:43.484 --> 03:46.617
[ Radio chatter ]

03:46.661 --> 03:49.403
-[ Groans ]
-Hey, sir? Sir, can you hear me?

03:49.446 --> 03:51.448
Sir?

03:51.492 --> 03:55.278
[ Radio chatter,
indistinct shouting ]

03:55.322 --> 03:56.888
[ Siren wailing ]

03:56.932 --> 03:58.238
All right,
what is your name, sir?

03:58.281 --> 04:01.284
Lars.
Captain Jonathan Larssen.

04:01.328 --> 04:02.633
Good.

04:02.677 --> 04:05.288
Where's my wife?

04:05.332 --> 04:07.290
Okay, we're gonna find her,
but right now, we need
to get you out of here.

04:07.334 --> 04:09.771
I'm gonna need a firefighter
over here!

04:09.814 --> 04:12.513
[ Indistinct shouting,
sirens wailing ]

04:12.556 --> 04:15.472
[ Horn honks ]

04:15.516 --> 04:18.519
[ Shouting continues,
radio chatter ]

04:18.562 --> 04:20.999
I got one up here!

04:21.043 --> 04:22.087
[ Grunts ]

04:22.131 --> 04:23.828
Shallow pulse.

04:23.872 --> 04:27.571
Help me get him down.
Gotta get him back to Angels.

04:27.615 --> 04:30.008
One, two...

04:30.052 --> 04:31.401
-Aah!
-Here's the good news.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.360
I can take this out without
severing the artery.

04:33.403 --> 04:35.927
You good with that?Not really, but you're gonna
do it anyway, aren't you?

04:35.971 --> 04:38.539
-Okay, bite down on that.
-[ Grunting ]

04:38.582 --> 04:41.498
[ Muffled screaming ][ Squish ]

04:41.542 --> 04:44.327
Let's go. It's not safe here.

04:44.371 --> 04:46.503
Is anyone else up here?!

04:46.547 --> 04:49.985
[ Siren whooping ]

04:50.028 --> 04:52.335
Over here!

04:52.379 --> 04:54.250
Man: [ Amplified voice ]
This is the Los Angeles Port...

04:54.294 --> 04:57.340
Hey, guys, there's someone
in the water!

04:57.384 --> 05:00.517
All marine craft, please stay
clear of the area.

05:00.561 --> 05:02.867
Willis!

05:02.911 --> 05:04.652
Wait a minute, wait, wait, wait,
where's my mom?

05:04.695 --> 05:07.611
-Your mom was in the boat?
-Yes.

05:07.655 --> 05:08.830
Willis, the boat's
leaking fuel!

05:08.873 --> 05:10.005
Wait here. Stay there.

05:10.048 --> 05:12.616
That's her. That's my mom.

05:12.660 --> 05:14.705
No! Let me get her.

05:14.749 --> 05:16.359
-No. No.
-Get off of me!

05:16.403 --> 05:19.493
-Too late. Too late!
-No!

05:19.536 --> 05:22.365
[ Siren wailing,
helicopter blades whirring ]

05:22.409 --> 05:23.366
♪♪

05:30.634 --> 05:35.378
[ Radio chatter,
siren wailing ]

05:35.422 --> 05:37.380
Where's my wife?

05:37.424 --> 05:39.034
Is she okay?

05:39.077 --> 05:42.254
We need to worry about you
right now.

05:42.298 --> 05:44.605
♪♪

05:44.648 --> 05:46.476
Hi, Sally.

05:46.520 --> 05:48.391
So Doug is still in surgery,

05:48.435 --> 05:50.175
and we won't know anything
for a little while.

05:50.219 --> 05:53.265
Did you talk
to my mom yet?

05:53.309 --> 05:54.832
Not yet.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.704
She can't answer the phone
while she's working.

05:56.747 --> 06:00.229
-Mm-hmm.
-I hope she gets here soon.

06:00.272 --> 06:02.666
I'm sure she will.

06:02.710 --> 06:06.453
♪♪

06:06.496 --> 06:09.891
Listen, I'm sorry.
She's gone.

06:09.934 --> 06:11.501
I gotta go help
your father.

06:11.545 --> 06:14.069
Do not tell him about
your mother, okay?

06:14.112 --> 06:16.158
What are you talking about?Do you understand
what I'm saying?

06:16.201 --> 06:17.725
Willis! Can I get some help
over here?!

06:17.768 --> 06:20.902
Not now, okay? Not now.

06:20.945 --> 06:25.341
♪♪

06:25.385 --> 06:26.908
[ Siren whooping ]

06:26.951 --> 06:30.041
[ Grunting ]

06:30.085 --> 06:33.001
No femoral pulse. This winch
is crushing his pelvis.

06:33.044 --> 06:35.395
But he still has circulation
north of his hips.

06:35.438 --> 06:37.440
We're gonna get you
out of here, sir.

06:37.484 --> 06:39.616
I -- how are you gonna
get a 1,200-pound
piece of steel off him?

06:39.660 --> 06:42.271
Get it together, Charlie.

06:42.314 --> 06:44.273
Okay, this mast is still
attached to the other boat.

06:44.316 --> 06:46.275
LAFD is gonna have to cut
the arm and lift it out.

06:46.318 --> 06:48.190
But when they do, all that
circulation's gonna run south,

06:48.233 --> 06:49.278
he's gonna code.

06:49.321 --> 06:52.977
Charlie, make sure
your mom's okay.

06:53.021 --> 06:55.719
♪♪

06:55.763 --> 06:57.329
Just do what I tell ya!

06:57.373 --> 07:00.811
[ Grunting ]

07:00.855 --> 07:02.596
I'm staying here with you.

07:02.639 --> 07:06.643
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

07:06.687 --> 07:10.299
♪♪

07:10.342 --> 07:13.737
Okay, start the insertion
at the mid-axillary line.

07:13.781 --> 07:15.130
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

07:15.173 --> 07:18.176
-Dad?
-Emily, don't look at this.

07:18.220 --> 07:19.351
Get back to my office.

07:19.395 --> 07:21.484
Am I supposed to
sit there all day?

07:21.528 --> 07:23.965
You have a book. Now go.

07:24.008 --> 07:25.270
Why can't I just call Mom?

07:25.314 --> 07:27.011
I'm not gonna get into this
right now.

07:27.055 --> 07:28.230
Can you see that
I have a patient?

07:28.273 --> 07:30.841
You always have a patient.

07:30.885 --> 07:34.671
-Oh, my God. How old is he?
-He's 8.

07:34.715 --> 07:36.847
What's wrong with him?

07:36.891 --> 07:39.284
He burned his throat on a dumb prank. Now go.

07:39.328 --> 07:42.331
Get outta here. Go.

07:42.374 --> 07:43.767
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

07:43.811 --> 07:48.163
-You okay?
-I'm fine. Focus.

07:48.206 --> 07:50.687
[ Door closes ]

07:50.731 --> 07:55.518
♪♪

07:55.562 --> 07:59.348
-Hello?
-Oh. Hi.

07:59.391 --> 08:02.003
I'm...not like some rando.

08:02.046 --> 08:04.266
Dr. Campbell's my father.
I'm Emily.

08:04.309 --> 08:06.747
Oh, hi. I'm Ariel.

08:06.790 --> 08:09.489
So you, like, work here?

08:09.532 --> 08:12.274
[ Clicks tongue ] Why is
everyone surprised by that?

08:12.317 --> 08:14.798
-[ Laughs ] Here.
-Oh. Thank you.

08:14.842 --> 08:18.585
[ Chuckles ] You know, I heard
two guys on the elevator

08:18.628 --> 08:20.108
talking about a guy upstairs

08:20.151 --> 08:21.979
with a cucumber
stuck in his butt.

08:22.023 --> 08:24.242
-What?
-[ Laughs ]

08:24.286 --> 08:26.288
-Oh, God.
-So gross.

08:26.331 --> 08:28.116
-Ew!
-[ Laughs ] I know, right?

08:28.159 --> 08:31.293
He was short of breath,
so I asked Marjorie

08:31.336 --> 08:34.992
to drive us here.Only one at the assisted living
with a license.

08:35.036 --> 08:36.994
I'm very popular.

08:37.038 --> 08:40.345
-You're wheezing.
-COPD.

08:40.389 --> 08:42.870
But it doesn't slow me down,
though, does it, Gloria?

08:42.913 --> 08:44.872
Harold,
you're embarrassing me.[ Hits leg ]

08:44.915 --> 08:48.571
150 milligrams of solumedrol
and start him on a nebulizer.

08:48.615 --> 08:50.268
You'll feel better soon.

08:50.312 --> 08:51.835
He had a little fever, too.

08:51.879 --> 08:54.229
I told you I run hot, Gloria.

08:54.272 --> 08:56.710
I'm gonna get him on a CBC,
do a chest X-ray,

08:56.753 --> 08:58.842
and then check his urine.

08:58.886 --> 09:00.931
You getting with that
pretty nurse?

09:00.975 --> 09:05.588
Doctor. And no.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.982
Not ever.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.506
[ Chuckles ]

09:10.550 --> 09:15.555
First guy you sent
from the boat crash? DOA.

09:15.598 --> 09:18.253
His sister's here.

09:18.296 --> 09:23.911
[ Siren wailing in distance,
radio chatter ]

09:23.954 --> 09:28.437
And I'm so sorry, but I need you
to verify this is your brother.

09:28.480 --> 09:31.353
[ Sighs ]

09:32.876 --> 09:35.400
[ Gasps ] Oh.

09:35.444 --> 09:40.231
Oh, God! [ Crying ]

09:40.275 --> 09:41.493
-That's him.
-Okay.

09:41.537 --> 09:42.625
Okay.

09:42.669 --> 09:45.410
[ Sobbing ]

09:45.454 --> 09:49.850
[ Gasping ]

09:49.893 --> 09:51.765
[ Sobbing ]

09:51.808 --> 09:55.029
I think I just need to go
sit somewhere.

09:55.072 --> 09:57.858
Is there a...

09:57.901 --> 10:00.512
a chapel?

10:00.556 --> 10:03.690
Yeah. Yeah,
I can take you there.

10:03.733 --> 10:05.300
[ Cries ]

10:05.343 --> 10:06.997
We have to call
Child Protective Services.

10:07.041 --> 10:08.956
I called the mom's office.
She was fired weeks ago.

10:08.999 --> 10:10.479
She has a gambling problem.

10:10.522 --> 10:13.090
She goes to the casino
for days at a time.

10:13.134 --> 10:16.006
Okay, wait, wait, wait,
hold on.

10:16.050 --> 10:17.442
I wanna talk to her first.
I wanna get all the facts.

10:17.486 --> 10:20.663
We'd have to hunt
her down first. Right?

10:20.707 --> 10:23.405
-That's not our job.
-She is their mother.

10:23.448 --> 10:25.973
And you're not. We have two
minors here without a guardian.

10:26.016 --> 10:28.453
One is in post-op.
Our job is to protect them.

10:28.497 --> 10:32.283
Make the call...or I will.

10:32.327 --> 10:35.330
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

10:35.373 --> 10:37.288
♪♪

10:37.332 --> 10:38.463
[ Buzzing ]

10:38.507 --> 10:39.987
Good.

10:40.030 --> 10:41.597
He's got a thready pulse.
We need more blood.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.644
Fire department says they need
20 minutes to get this off him.

10:44.687 --> 10:45.819
We don't have 20 minutes.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.821
Charlie, if we can't
get this off him,

10:47.864 --> 10:49.474
is there a way to
lower the boat?

10:49.518 --> 10:52.564
Charlie! Is there a way
to lower the boat?

10:52.608 --> 10:54.305
I don't know. Uh, yeah.

10:54.349 --> 10:57.091
Yeah. I can reverse
the bilge pump.
She'll take on water.

10:57.134 --> 10:59.136
You've been trying to
sink this boat for years.

10:59.180 --> 11:00.398
Not now, Dad.

11:00.442 --> 11:02.662
Hey, I'm the one under
a pile of ship here.

11:02.705 --> 11:03.924
I'll say whatever
the hell I want.

11:03.967 --> 11:05.926
You should go back to
your fancy bank job.

11:05.969 --> 11:08.929
-Leave this to the men.
-No offense taken.

11:08.972 --> 11:12.715
He was here to foreclose
on the boat. My boat.

11:12.759 --> 11:14.543
It wasn't me.
It was the bank.

11:14.586 --> 11:15.762
You work for the bank,
don't you?

11:15.805 --> 11:17.720
Yes, but I don't make
the decisions.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.809
God, do you ever stop?!Hey, hey, Charlie, Charlie,
this isn't the time.

11:19.853 --> 11:23.117
I really need your help
with the bilge pump.

11:23.160 --> 11:28.035
Me and Harriet, we were gonna
retire on this boat.

11:28.078 --> 11:31.038
But you didn't have the guts
to tell her yourself!

11:31.081 --> 11:33.388
♪♪

11:33.431 --> 11:36.434
It'll break her heart
when I tell her.

11:36.478 --> 11:39.046
You listening, Charlie?

11:39.089 --> 11:41.439
She'll never
speak to you again!

11:41.483 --> 11:44.747
You listening to me?!

11:44.791 --> 11:46.444
Yeah, well, she's never gonna
speak to me again anyway, okay,

11:46.488 --> 11:49.796
'cause she's dead.
All right? Mom's dead!

11:52.276 --> 11:55.671
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

11:55.715 --> 11:57.586
-Dad?
-He's hemorrhaging!

11:57.629 --> 11:59.588
Dad!

11:59.631 --> 12:00.632
♪♪

12:05.550 --> 12:07.335
[ Buzzing ]

12:07.378 --> 12:09.685
Charlie, is there any way to
speed this whole thing up?

12:09.729 --> 12:11.687
I reversed the pump.
She's taking on water.

12:11.731 --> 12:12.732
I don't know what else!

12:12.775 --> 12:14.777
Willis, his pulse is
barely there.

12:14.821 --> 12:16.648
God,
I shouldn't have told him.

12:16.692 --> 12:19.651
What's done is done.You think this is my fault,
don't you?

12:19.695 --> 12:21.305
I didn't say that.

12:21.349 --> 12:22.785
[ Radio chatter ]

12:22.829 --> 12:25.135
[ Whispers ] You think this is
really gonna work?

12:25.179 --> 12:27.007
It has to.

12:27.050 --> 12:29.183
♪♪

12:33.274 --> 12:36.930
Stay as long as you like.
I really am sorry.

12:36.973 --> 12:38.670
Could you sit with me
for a moment?

12:40.585 --> 12:43.632
Uh, I can get the chaplain,
but I really have to get back.

12:43.675 --> 12:47.462
Please. You don't have
to pray, just sit.

12:47.505 --> 12:49.725
Okay.

12:52.162 --> 12:53.729
[ Door closes ]

12:53.773 --> 12:57.864
♪♪

12:57.907 --> 13:00.344
[ Sighs ]

13:00.388 --> 13:02.869
I'm not religious at all.

13:02.912 --> 13:05.001
Me neither.

13:05.045 --> 13:06.916
Why'd you wanna come in?

13:06.960 --> 13:10.572
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't know where else to go.

13:10.615 --> 13:14.358
Do I go home and what would I do
when I got there?

13:14.402 --> 13:16.839
I mean, do I get the mail?

13:16.883 --> 13:18.580
I mean, what an insult
it would be to my brother

13:18.623 --> 13:20.800
to get the stupid mail
the day he died.

13:20.843 --> 13:24.760
♪♪

13:24.804 --> 13:26.806
I know you have to go.

13:26.849 --> 13:30.505
♪♪

13:30.548 --> 13:32.768
I really am sorry.

13:34.901 --> 13:36.859
I'll let the chaplain
know you're here.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.340
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

13:39.383 --> 13:42.038
Um, excuse me.
I'm Pamela Kessler.

13:42.082 --> 13:44.258
I'm looking for my kids,
Doug and Sally.

13:44.301 --> 13:45.781
I was told they were here.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.827
We've been trying to reach you.

13:47.870 --> 13:50.742
Yeah, I'm -- I'm sorry.
I just got the message.

13:50.786 --> 13:51.961
Is Doug okay?

13:52.005 --> 13:55.443
You're gonna need to speak
with Dr. Rorish.

13:55.486 --> 13:56.879
♪♪

13:56.923 --> 13:58.315
-Wait. Surgery?
-Yes.

13:58.359 --> 14:00.796
I don't understand.
You said he drank hot water.

14:00.840 --> 14:03.886
Boiling water
through a straw.

14:03.930 --> 14:06.715
His esophagus needed
extensive reconstruction.

14:06.758 --> 14:11.633
But he's young, he's healthy,
and hopefully, he'll recover.

14:11.676 --> 14:16.116
Hopefully? And where's --
where's Sally?

14:16.159 --> 14:17.900
Where are my kids?

14:17.944 --> 14:19.554
They're here,
and they're safe.

14:19.597 --> 14:22.905
But Child Protective Services
is opening an investigation.

14:22.949 --> 14:25.299
Wait. What?
You -- you called them?

14:25.342 --> 14:28.737
I did. It's standard
in incidents like this.

14:28.780 --> 14:31.392
Wait, hang on, hang on.
I had to work. Okay?

14:31.435 --> 14:34.830
My mother couldn't come --
What -- what else was
I supposed to do?

14:34.874 --> 14:36.571
Okay, Pamela, we spoke
to your boss.

14:36.614 --> 14:38.921
We know
you weren't at work.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.923
You don't know me. You don't
know anything about me.

14:40.967 --> 14:42.925
You don't know anything
about my kids!

14:42.969 --> 14:46.668
-You weren't there for them.
-I demand to see my kids!

14:46.711 --> 14:51.325
I'll get security.No, no. Please, please.
That's not necessary.

14:51.368 --> 14:53.240
[ Sighs ]

14:53.283 --> 14:54.763
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

14:54.806 --> 14:56.765
Please.

14:56.808 --> 15:00.769
My kids need me.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.728
Please.

15:05.992 --> 15:07.515
-Feel that?
-Yeah.

15:07.558 --> 15:10.779
Is that okay?
Oh, here we are.

15:10.822 --> 15:13.347
Phoebe, this is Dr. Leighton,
one of our surgical residents.

15:13.390 --> 15:16.263
Well, thank you for coming.
I need an ex-lap.

15:16.306 --> 15:20.397
[ Laughs ] Okay, hold on
a minute. What's going on?

15:20.441 --> 15:23.052
Abdominal pain, tenderness in
the lower left quadrant.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.968
And what makes you think
it's surgical?

15:26.012 --> 15:27.970
I swallowed
a bunch of tacks.

15:28.014 --> 15:31.582
Way to bury the lede.
What does the X-ray show?

15:31.626 --> 15:33.584
Well, so far, no perforations.

15:33.628 --> 15:35.586
I'm gonna examine you,
Phoebe.

15:35.630 --> 15:39.808
It's okay. Relax. Just relax.

15:39.851 --> 15:41.984
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:42.028 --> 15:46.249
Well, the abdomen
is still soft. That's good.

15:46.293 --> 15:48.556
Your chart here says you've had
several psych evaluations

15:48.599 --> 15:50.166
over the years.
-Excuse me?

15:50.210 --> 15:52.908
It's a form of OCD.
I can't help myself.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.954
-Am I getting the surgery?
-No.

15:54.997 --> 15:57.043
But it hurts.
I want the surgery.

15:57.086 --> 15:58.435
And you've got three scars
to prove that.

15:58.479 --> 16:00.133
I'm sorry, Phoebe. You're not
having surgery today.

16:00.176 --> 16:01.699
Most likely the tacks
will pass on their own,

16:01.743 --> 16:04.441
but, Dr. Guthrie, let me know
if that changes, okay?

16:04.485 --> 16:06.269
Excuse me, Phoebe.

16:06.313 --> 16:10.012
Dr. Leighton,
I need a word with you.

16:10.056 --> 16:12.667
I called you for a surgical
consult, not a psychiatric one.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.103
Or maybe I should've called
Dr. Campbell.

16:14.147 --> 16:16.149
Call him. I'm not clogging up
the OR schedule

16:16.192 --> 16:18.238
with an unnecessary surgery.

16:18.281 --> 16:19.979
Let me know if she perfs.

16:22.720 --> 16:25.854
How we doing, Charlie?She dropped about
2 or 3 inches.

16:25.897 --> 16:27.856
Yeah, I could see some space.
We're getting close.

16:27.899 --> 16:29.162
All right, let's get that
Stryker ready

16:29.205 --> 16:31.903
and bring me a backboard.

16:31.947 --> 16:33.644
[ Whirring ]

16:33.688 --> 16:36.038
-He's crashing.
-Okay, we're free. We're free!

16:36.082 --> 16:37.518
Come on, let's get him
out of here.

16:37.561 --> 16:40.042
-Okay, let's go. Careful.
-All right. On my count.

16:40.086 --> 16:42.958
One...two...three.[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

16:43.002 --> 16:44.177
Let's get him to Angels.

16:44.220 --> 16:46.048
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:46.092 --> 16:47.484
Come on, Charlie. You, too.

16:47.528 --> 16:50.879
No, no, he doesn't want me here.I'm not asking.

16:50.922 --> 16:53.055
No, no, I can't.If he doesn't make it to
the hospital,

16:53.099 --> 16:54.317
you're gonna regret not
being with him

16:54.361 --> 16:56.885
for the rest of your life.

16:56.928 --> 16:58.278
You understand?

16:58.321 --> 17:01.411
♪♪

17:01.455 --> 17:06.808
[ Exhales deeply ] Oh, that
thing worked like gangbusters.

17:06.851 --> 17:08.897
You did good, Red.

17:08.940 --> 17:11.639
There's just one other thing.
[ Clears throat ]

17:11.682 --> 17:15.382
You tested positive
for gonorrhea.

17:15.425 --> 17:16.557
Crap.

17:16.600 --> 17:18.167
It's easily cured
with doxycycline,

17:18.211 --> 17:21.649
but we strongly suggest you
inform your sexual partner.

17:21.692 --> 17:25.087
Yeah. Gloria, come here.
I got the clap!

17:25.131 --> 17:27.002
Shh! Keep your voice down.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.003
Who's listenin'?

17:28.047 --> 17:30.571
Which one is the clap?
Syphilis?

17:30.614 --> 17:33.922
No. Gonorrhea. It's...
way better.

17:33.965 --> 17:37.099
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

17:37.143 --> 17:39.058
[ Lowered voice ] Hey, uh,
call the nursing home.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.799
There's gonna be
a gonorrhea tornado.

17:41.843 --> 17:44.019
-What are you talking about?
-My man here is a player.

17:44.063 --> 17:47.066
-Come on. He's 80.
-Game recognizes game, Red.

17:47.109 --> 17:52.201
Excuse me. But I just
heard what Harold said.

17:52.245 --> 17:54.943
I think I need to
get tested, too.

17:55.987 --> 17:58.816
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

17:58.860 --> 18:01.602
He lost pulse en route.
Let's get him hooked up
to a monitor.

18:01.645 --> 18:04.431
-Another amp of epi.
-On it.

18:04.474 --> 18:07.651
♪♪

18:07.695 --> 18:10.132
Trace pericardial effusion,
poor cardiac activity.

18:10.176 --> 18:11.960
-Where's Charlie?
-Who?

18:12.003 --> 18:14.354
His son.
Should be here.

18:14.397 --> 18:16.225
[ Compressions pounding ]

18:16.269 --> 18:21.361
♪♪

18:21.404 --> 18:22.927
[ Monitor beeping rapidly,
paddles charge ]

18:22.971 --> 18:25.626
Ah, let's do it. Clear.

18:25.669 --> 18:27.976
Clear.[ Thump ]

18:28.019 --> 18:31.153
Okay, pulse is back.
Sinus tach. O2 sats at 78.

18:31.197 --> 18:33.068
Come on. Come on.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.592
Poor sonographic window.
I can't see.

18:35.636 --> 18:38.073
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

18:38.117 --> 18:41.598
Give me an 18 gauge.
The son should be here!

18:41.642 --> 18:44.819
♪♪

18:44.862 --> 18:48.170
He's gone.

18:48.214 --> 18:50.259
[ Click, thud ]

18:50.303 --> 18:52.609
♪♪

18:52.653 --> 18:54.916
[ Monitor beeps ]Sats improving.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.614
Okay, good. Let's get
a chest tube in him.
Get him packed up for the OR.

18:57.658 --> 19:00.356
-Hey.
-Hey.

19:00.400 --> 19:02.619
I feel like I haven't
seen you all day.

19:02.663 --> 19:04.143
I've just been busy.
That's all.

19:04.186 --> 19:06.101
-Everything okay?
-Fine.

19:06.145 --> 19:08.364
Heard you lost
a patient today.

19:08.408 --> 19:10.845
Yeah, I know. I was there.

19:10.888 --> 19:13.108
Day didn't start
great either.

19:13.152 --> 19:14.936
What do you mean?

19:14.979 --> 19:16.198
We fought.
Don't you remember?

19:16.242 --> 19:18.113
No, whatever it was,
it's fine.

19:18.157 --> 19:21.464
-Second time you've said "fine."
-What's wrong with "fine"?

19:21.508 --> 19:23.597
"Good" means good.
"Great" means great.

19:23.640 --> 19:26.643
-"Fine" never means fine.
-Just give me a break, okay?

19:26.687 --> 19:29.864
-Come on. Don't --
-My dad died a year ago today.

19:29.907 --> 19:32.171
What?

19:33.781 --> 19:36.131
Why didn't you tell me?

19:36.175 --> 19:38.873
Because...I'm fine.

19:38.916 --> 19:41.658
♪♪

19:41.702 --> 19:44.139
What's wrong?
You have to tell me.

19:44.183 --> 19:47.621
-Whoa. What...Excuse me.
-You can tell me. It's okay.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.231
You're not supposed to have
any contact right now.

19:49.275 --> 19:52.191
Something's wrong with her.
Something's wrong.Let me see.

19:52.234 --> 19:54.454
Her voice. It's strange.
And -- and she's hot.

19:54.497 --> 19:56.717
-Get me Dr. Rorish!
-Sally?

19:56.760 --> 19:58.371
Sally, honey, can you tell
Mama the truth?

19:58.414 --> 20:01.417
Did you do the dare, too?It's all my fault.
I did it first.

20:01.461 --> 20:04.986
-Doug was just copying me.
-What's the problem?

20:05.029 --> 20:07.249
-She did it, too.
-[ Crying ] I'm sorry, Mom.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.120
Sally, can you open
your mouth, please?

20:09.164 --> 20:11.297
Okay, she's got blisters
on her throat.

20:11.340 --> 20:14.125
She may have perforated
like her brother.
Gurney.

20:14.169 --> 20:16.084
-Oh, my God!
-Call Dr. Campbell!

20:16.127 --> 20:17.346
Oh, my God.

20:17.390 --> 20:19.174
What's happening?
What -- what is happening?

20:19.218 --> 20:20.697
-[ Choking ]
-I need to assess her.

20:20.741 --> 20:23.265
-You have to save her. Please.
-[ Choking ]

20:23.309 --> 20:24.832
You can't let anything
happen to her.

20:24.875 --> 20:26.964
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You need to wait here.

20:27.008 --> 20:29.489
That's my daughter. Please.Security! Park this woman
right here till we get back.

20:29.532 --> 20:31.534
Sally! Sal...

20:37.236 --> 20:41.022
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

20:41.065 --> 20:42.632
[ Door closes ]

20:42.676 --> 20:44.286
Sally's in surgery.

20:44.330 --> 20:48.377
Uh, she has severe burns
in her throat.

20:48.421 --> 20:49.944
Um, it'll be a couple hours,

20:49.987 --> 20:53.295
but I promise you
I'll keep you updated, okay?

20:53.339 --> 20:56.429
I never meant for
any of this to happen.

20:56.472 --> 21:01.129
♪♪

21:01.172 --> 21:06.090
They're gonna...
take them from me.

21:06.134 --> 21:08.223
[ Voice breaking ]
Aren't they?

21:08.267 --> 21:12.445
I think everybody wants
what's best for Sally and Doug.

21:12.488 --> 21:14.447
I think that's what
you want, too.

21:14.490 --> 21:18.146
[ Sighs ] I just...I just don't
wanna lose them.

21:18.189 --> 21:20.844
Then you're going to
have to change.

21:20.888 --> 21:23.064
You're going to have to
take responsibility.

21:23.107 --> 21:27.503
You're going to have to
fight for them.

21:27.547 --> 21:29.418
♪♪

21:29.462 --> 21:31.377
[ Exhales deeply ][ Door closes ]

21:34.380 --> 21:38.558
[ Clattering ]

21:38.601 --> 21:40.951
What?

21:40.995 --> 21:44.215
You know, Freud says we cast
people around us

21:44.259 --> 21:47.697
to replay the stuff in our lives
we couldn't fix before.

21:47.741 --> 21:49.351
What does that even mean?

21:49.395 --> 21:51.571
Ask Freud.

21:51.614 --> 21:53.486
I'm asking you.

21:53.529 --> 21:56.967
We see a lot of stuff.
Horrible things.

21:57.011 --> 22:01.450
What is it about this that's
getting under your skin?

22:01.494 --> 22:04.714
He should be stronger --
Charlie.

22:04.758 --> 22:06.977
You don't even know him.

22:07.021 --> 22:09.415
I know a son should
be there for his father.

22:09.458 --> 22:11.155
Who are we talking about
right now?

22:11.199 --> 22:13.549
I don't know. Who are you
talking about right now?

22:13.593 --> 22:16.160
Freud.

22:16.204 --> 22:21.209
♪♪

22:21.252 --> 22:25.387
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

22:25.431 --> 22:29.260
So let me get this straight --
did he try to kiss or not?

22:29.304 --> 22:31.393
I mean, I think so.
I couldn't really tell.

22:31.437 --> 22:34.527
He either did this...
[ Kisses ] Or he didn't.

22:34.570 --> 22:37.573
It was, like, in more,
like, slow motion.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.314
You have to take charge.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.489
-Me?
-Yeah, why not?

22:40.533 --> 22:43.623
Why do they get to make
all the choices?

22:43.666 --> 22:45.668
You ever kissed
a boy before?

22:45.712 --> 22:47.975
Yeah, totally.

22:48.018 --> 22:49.324
Me, too.

22:49.368 --> 22:52.588
I'm totally lying.
[ Laughs ]

22:52.632 --> 22:54.242
[ Giggles ] Me, too.

22:54.285 --> 22:55.765
Wait, so you haven't?

22:55.809 --> 22:57.637
I have spina bifida,
remember?

22:57.680 --> 23:00.596
-So what?
-So boys aren't into that.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.859
Boys are stupid.

23:02.903 --> 23:05.862
Hey.

23:05.906 --> 23:08.778
[ Both giggling ]

23:08.822 --> 23:12.303
Doxycycline, 100 milligrams,
two times a day.

23:12.347 --> 23:15.568
You English whore.

23:15.611 --> 23:17.744
-Whoa.
-He liked me first,

23:17.787 --> 23:19.702
but you had to go and get
your hooks into him.

23:19.746 --> 23:21.312
Okay, ladies, please.

23:21.356 --> 23:22.618
Why do women always
attack each other?

23:22.662 --> 23:26.492
It's on him, too. I mean,
girl power, right?

23:28.058 --> 23:29.669
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

23:29.712 --> 23:32.236
We're best friends.
How could you do this to me?

23:32.280 --> 23:34.369
I'm sorry.

23:34.413 --> 23:35.805
But it had been so long,
and he --

23:35.849 --> 23:38.678
he made me feel young again.

23:38.721 --> 23:41.245
-He has a gift.
-[ Clears throat ] Okay. Um...

23:41.289 --> 23:43.683
I hate to pour gasoline
on this fire,

23:43.726 --> 23:46.816
but have either one of you had
any other sexual partners?

23:46.860 --> 23:49.428
-Hell, no!
-Watch your mouth.

23:49.471 --> 23:50.733
What about Harold?

23:50.777 --> 23:54.433
♪♪

23:54.476 --> 23:56.435
So she's a friend of yours?

23:56.478 --> 23:59.133
Yeah, I mean, we just met,
but she's really cool so...

24:02.179 --> 24:04.138
Did I freak you out
this morning?

24:04.181 --> 24:08.316
♪♪

24:08.359 --> 24:09.883
[ Gasps ]

24:11.667 --> 24:14.017
Wait. Uh, w-was that okay?

24:14.061 --> 24:16.019
I'm not like a --
like a slut or anything?

24:16.063 --> 24:19.153
Oh, no! No, that was great.
Of course.

24:19.196 --> 24:22.939
Um...how was it for you?

24:22.983 --> 24:24.463
'Cause...

24:24.506 --> 24:28.554
I feel like...
I can do better.

24:28.597 --> 24:32.514
Um, me, too.

24:32.558 --> 24:38.085
♪♪

24:38.128 --> 24:40.522
-Max?
-Dad, what are you doing here?

24:40.566 --> 24:42.263
I said I'd be right back.

24:42.306 --> 24:44.265
Who's this?

24:44.308 --> 24:45.832
This is Ariel.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.703
She's a candy striper
and my friend.

24:47.747 --> 24:50.097
Girlfriend.

24:50.140 --> 24:51.272
[ Whispers ] Girlfriend?

24:51.315 --> 24:53.143
Well, nice to meet you,
Ariel.

24:53.187 --> 24:55.102
Do you mind if I speak
to my son in private?

24:55.145 --> 24:58.148
Sure, I gotta go to work
anyway, so...

24:58.192 --> 25:02.631
♪♪

25:02.675 --> 25:04.285
[ Door closes ]

25:05.721 --> 25:08.681
I was looking for you.[ Telephone ringing ]

25:08.724 --> 25:10.378
Told me
I needed some head scan.

25:10.421 --> 25:13.076
-Where's my dad?
-He's in surgery.

25:13.120 --> 25:14.643
Well, how is he?

25:14.687 --> 25:16.819
That's all the information
I have right now.

25:19.474 --> 25:21.563
We have nothing in common.

25:25.088 --> 25:28.439
That's not true.

25:29.789 --> 25:32.443
You both loved your mom.

25:34.141 --> 25:35.708
Now she's gone.

25:37.840 --> 25:40.800
Which means the two of you
are all you have left.

25:40.843 --> 25:47.633
♪♪

25:47.676 --> 25:51.201
[ Coins dropping ]

25:53.116 --> 25:55.641
Excuse me, Dr. Rorish.

25:55.684 --> 25:57.120
I'm Owen Edwards,
Max's father.

25:57.164 --> 25:59.732
Oh! Hi.
It's really nice to meet --

25:59.775 --> 26:02.343
I just found Ariel
kissing my son.

26:02.386 --> 26:05.607
Well, surely Max was also
kissing Ariel.

26:05.651 --> 26:08.828
My son is a patient here,
and Ariel is an employee.

26:08.871 --> 26:10.743
I find that relationship
highly inappropriate.

26:10.786 --> 26:12.571
Okay, well, I really don't
think that you need to --

26:12.614 --> 26:14.964
Max has pulmonary
adenocarcinoma in situ.

26:15.008 --> 26:16.966
We have been on the lung
transplant waiting list

26:17.010 --> 26:18.881
for over a year.

26:18.925 --> 26:20.970
He needs to focus
on his health.

26:21.014 --> 26:22.929
I understand that this is
very difficult for you.

26:22.972 --> 26:24.757
She's preying on a sick kid.

26:24.800 --> 26:28.587
Now as a doctor and a mother,
it's your responsibility.

26:28.630 --> 26:30.937
Keep her away from my son.

26:30.980 --> 26:33.809
-Are we clear?
-Crystal.

26:33.853 --> 26:36.769
♪♪

26:36.812 --> 26:39.685
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

26:39.728 --> 26:41.643
Don't hit him. Hit me.

26:41.687 --> 26:44.124
I just helped tear two kids
away from their mother.

26:44.167 --> 26:46.692
I got reamed by Max's father.[ Wrapper rustling ]

26:46.735 --> 26:49.477
And my case worker says
I'm a bad mother.

26:49.520 --> 26:51.261
You're bad
at a lot of things.

26:51.305 --> 26:53.612
Mothering isn't one
of them.

26:53.655 --> 26:56.440
Oh, yeah?
What am I bad at?

26:56.484 --> 27:00.227
Okay. I got a list right here.[ Paper crinkles ]

27:00.270 --> 27:04.187
Wait, wait. Oh, don't read
number seven! Please!

27:04.231 --> 27:06.363
Now I need you
to listen to me, Phoebe.

27:06.407 --> 27:08.539
Your bowel has ruptured.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.150
And these people are gonna
take you up to sur--

27:10.193 --> 27:11.717
What the hell
is going on here?

27:11.760 --> 27:14.415
I just heard Dr. Sistulli was
paged for a perfed bowel.

27:14.458 --> 27:16.286
That's right. You're not the
only surgeon in this hospital.

27:16.330 --> 27:18.854
-She is my patient.
-No, she's not. Remember?

27:18.898 --> 27:21.857
You didn't want her.
So I got somebody else.

27:21.901 --> 27:25.774
Now if you'll excuse me,
Dr. Leighton. Let's go.

27:25.818 --> 27:30.692
♪♪

27:30.736 --> 27:32.912
Where did you get gonorrhea?

27:32.955 --> 27:35.088
'Cause it wasn't from
either of us.

27:35.131 --> 27:38.874
I have no idea. But listen,

27:38.918 --> 27:42.922
I'm old as dirt,
and you ain't much younger.

27:42.965 --> 27:46.403
So now do we really wanna spend
any more time fighting?

27:46.447 --> 27:50.190
Or do we wanna have
some fun?

27:50.233 --> 27:51.887
[ Sighs ]

27:51.931 --> 27:54.760
♪♪

27:54.803 --> 27:57.893
[ Sighs ]

27:57.937 --> 28:01.418
We've shared a lot of things
over the years.

28:01.462 --> 28:06.685
♪♪

28:06.728 --> 28:08.643
I can live with it
if you can.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.253
Share him?

28:10.297 --> 28:11.820
Deal.

28:11.864 --> 28:14.867
But not at the same time.
I'm not into that.

28:14.910 --> 28:17.217
[ Laughs ]

28:17.260 --> 28:20.394
[ Lowered voice ]
Harold is my spirit animal.

28:20.437 --> 28:21.787
For sure.

28:21.830 --> 28:27.662
♪♪

28:27.706 --> 28:30.186
You're gonna be fine. Okay?
Okay, just breathe.

28:30.230 --> 28:31.535
Look at me. Look at me.

28:31.579 --> 28:33.624
-Oh, God.
-[ Wheezing ]

28:33.668 --> 28:35.670
-Get help.
-[ Gasping ]

28:41.545 --> 28:42.808
What happened?He started having
trouble breathing.

28:42.851 --> 28:45.985
I counted 36 breaths per minute.Good job, Ariel.

28:46.028 --> 28:47.638
All right, I need you girls
to stay back there.

28:47.682 --> 28:50.119
Max, you stay with me, buddy.
Stay with me.

28:50.163 --> 28:51.730
Clear the way!

28:51.773 --> 28:55.255
[ Gasping and wheezing ]

28:55.298 --> 28:57.257
He's not moving any air
at all.

28:57.300 --> 28:59.128
We're here for you.Okay, let's get him on a
continuous nebulizer treatment,

28:59.172 --> 29:00.826
15 milligrams albuterol.
-Right away.

29:00.869 --> 29:03.785
He needs a continuous treatment.We're doing that right now.

29:03.829 --> 29:06.745
-[ Gasps ]
-Okay, here we go.

29:06.788 --> 29:08.659
-Okay? That's good.
-Want a bipap now?

29:08.703 --> 29:11.140
Not yet. Have it standing by
just in case.

29:11.184 --> 29:12.838
-[ Gasping ]
-Not yet.

29:12.881 --> 29:16.667
[ Wheezing ]

29:16.711 --> 29:18.931
Oh, God.

29:18.974 --> 29:23.805
[ Wheezing continues ]

29:23.849 --> 29:29.463
[ Max grunting ]

29:29.506 --> 29:31.900
[ Wheezing and grunting
continue ]

29:31.944 --> 29:37.558
Ariel, it's okay. This happens.
This isn't your fault.

29:37.601 --> 29:40.474
-It's not your fault.
-Okay.

29:40.517 --> 29:42.650
[ Gasping ]

29:42.693 --> 29:44.695
[ Beeping ]

29:44.739 --> 29:46.393
Sats are improving.

29:46.436 --> 29:48.264
-He's gonna be all right.
-[ Gasps ]

29:48.308 --> 29:50.136
He's stable.
We're gonna take him into Sides.

29:50.179 --> 29:52.660
Incoming!

29:52.703 --> 29:55.489
What happened?Charlie was in the CT scanner.
Started to seize.

29:55.532 --> 29:57.491
Gave him 2 of ativan
five minutes ago.

29:57.534 --> 29:59.798
Give him 2 more, give him
3 milligrams of dilantin.

29:59.841 --> 30:01.669
CT show anything?

30:01.712 --> 30:03.845
Starting seizing before
they could finish the scan.

30:03.889 --> 30:06.543
Need that CT. Okay, keep loading
him up on the anti-epileptics.

30:06.587 --> 30:08.023
We gotta stop these seizures.

30:08.067 --> 30:09.677
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

30:09.720 --> 30:12.506
It's the second kid today.

30:12.549 --> 30:15.726
Second kid,
same woman's negligence.

30:15.770 --> 30:17.424
Sutures are holding.

30:17.467 --> 30:19.469
Let's get ready to
close her up.

30:19.513 --> 30:21.254
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

30:21.297 --> 30:23.517
Heart rate's 140.
Pressure's dropping.

30:23.560 --> 30:26.737
-Did you hit a vessel?
-No, there's no blood.

30:26.781 --> 30:28.696
Heart rate's 200.[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

30:28.739 --> 30:32.004
No bleeding, no air embolus.
What is it, Dr. Leighton?

30:32.047 --> 30:34.180
Reaction to the anesthesia?No. She's in
a hypokalemic rhythm

30:34.223 --> 30:35.834
from too much vomiting.

30:35.877 --> 30:37.836
Crash cart now.
She's going to arrest.

30:39.402 --> 30:41.404
Still not responding
to the meds.

30:41.448 --> 30:43.798
We need to paralyze
and intubate him.Not yet.

30:43.842 --> 30:45.887
We're risking
permanent brain damage
if this goes on any longer.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.802
It's time to induce a coma.

30:47.846 --> 30:50.892
Need 4 more milligrams
of ativan, 3 of keppra.Wait, what?

30:50.936 --> 30:53.764
You're playing the odds
with a man's brain.

30:53.808 --> 30:57.768
Charlie will die
if we don't act now.
Shut up!

30:57.812 --> 31:00.206
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]Willis, I am pushing propofol.

31:00.249 --> 31:02.251
His brain
can't take it anymore.

31:02.295 --> 31:03.383
You do not touch
this patient.

31:03.426 --> 31:04.688
You once told me there was
a difference

31:04.732 --> 31:06.865
between being a cowboy
and being reckless.

31:06.908 --> 31:09.476
Which one are you right now,
huh? He is going to die.

31:09.519 --> 31:11.782
[ Beeps ]

31:11.826 --> 31:14.873
♪♪

31:14.916 --> 31:17.658
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

31:17.701 --> 31:19.529
How did you know?

31:19.573 --> 31:21.314
Sometimes you just
have your gut.

31:21.357 --> 31:23.577
All right, let's get him
up to CT, make sure
there isn't a bleed.

31:23.620 --> 31:24.752
And what I said was
there's a difference

31:24.795 --> 31:27.537
between being a cowboy
and an idiot.

31:27.581 --> 31:30.366
I'm an attending physician.
You're a resident.

31:30.410 --> 31:32.194
Don't ever contradict me
in here again.

31:32.238 --> 31:37.025
♪♪

31:37.069 --> 31:40.942
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

31:40.986 --> 31:42.944
No organized
cardiac activity.

31:42.988 --> 31:44.815
Ready to shock.

31:44.859 --> 31:46.600
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

31:46.643 --> 31:48.123
[ Thump ]

31:48.167 --> 31:51.822
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

31:51.866 --> 31:55.914
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

31:55.957 --> 31:57.176
Pulse is back.

31:57.219 --> 31:58.786
It worked.[ Paddles thud ]

31:58.829 --> 32:00.266
You don't seem happy.

32:00.309 --> 32:03.878
♪♪

32:03.922 --> 32:05.967
Just close her up.

32:06.011 --> 32:07.926
[ Door opens ]

32:10.145 --> 32:11.930
[ Garbage can clanks ]

32:11.973 --> 32:13.888
She's gonna be okay.

32:16.108 --> 32:19.241
I want her mother to see her.

32:19.285 --> 32:21.156
Before you say anything,

32:21.200 --> 32:23.637
she came back
when it mattered the most.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.901
Yes, protecting those kids
is our job.

32:26.945 --> 32:29.469
Punishing their mother
is not.

32:32.776 --> 32:35.518
Will, trust me.

32:35.562 --> 32:37.999
You start being punitive,

32:38.043 --> 32:40.871
and it's a very difficult hole
to climb out of.

32:40.915 --> 32:45.354
♪♪

32:45.398 --> 32:47.356
[ Door closes ]

32:56.452 --> 33:00.500
My dad died because he took
terrible care of himself.

33:00.543 --> 33:03.982
There was no higher
or lower power at play.

33:04.025 --> 33:07.811
Isn't a higher power kind of
part of the 12 step deal?

33:07.855 --> 33:11.641
Yeah, it just seems crazy.

33:11.685 --> 33:14.035
What's God gonna say to me?

33:14.079 --> 33:17.647
Maybe it isn't about
hearing God.

33:17.691 --> 33:20.085
Maybe it's just about being
in a place

33:20.128 --> 33:22.478
where you can
listen to yourself.

33:22.522 --> 33:30.399
♪♪

33:33.098 --> 33:34.273
[ Door closes ]

33:34.316 --> 33:37.232
-I feel stupid.
-We're the only ones here.

33:37.276 --> 33:39.408
[ Sighs ]

33:41.323 --> 33:44.457
Mr. Savetti, it's Noa.

33:44.500 --> 33:46.720
I'm sleeping with your son.

33:55.250 --> 33:58.384
Hey, Dad.

33:58.427 --> 33:59.994
I, uh...

34:01.604 --> 34:03.650
I wish things had been
better with us.

34:03.693 --> 34:07.001
I wish
we had had more time.

34:07.045 --> 34:09.612
♪♪

34:09.656 --> 34:13.138
Maybe we could've
figured it out.

34:14.574 --> 34:16.880
I miss you.

34:16.924 --> 34:26.890
♪♪

34:26.934 --> 34:29.371
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

34:29.415 --> 34:30.938
-Whoa, whoa, easy.
-[ Exhales deeply ]

34:30.981 --> 34:32.766
You still have anesthesia
in you.

34:32.809 --> 34:35.160
[ Exhales deeply ]
Where's my boy?

34:35.203 --> 34:37.684
Where's Charlie?

34:37.727 --> 34:39.425
He's right there.

34:39.468 --> 34:43.429
He had a seizure.
But he's gonna be fine.

34:43.472 --> 34:46.475
A seizure? Why -- why a seizure?

34:46.519 --> 34:48.086
He had
a traumatic brain injury.

34:48.129 --> 34:52.133
But the good news is the CT
doesn't show any bleed.

34:52.177 --> 34:53.700
Is he gonna be okay?

34:53.743 --> 34:55.571
Yeah. He's gonna have to be
in the hospital for a few days,

34:55.615 --> 34:57.182
but he should be fine.

34:57.225 --> 35:00.489
[ Exhales deeply ]I'll tell you what
he does need.

35:00.533 --> 35:03.188
[ Exhales deeply ] What?

35:03.231 --> 35:04.885
His father.

35:04.928 --> 35:07.105
He has his father.
He knows that.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.150
Does he?

35:09.194 --> 35:12.153
[ Sighs ] Fine.

35:12.197 --> 35:13.981
So I don't hug him
all the time

35:14.024 --> 35:17.027
or tell him I love him
twice a day like his mom does.

35:17.071 --> 35:21.336
Boo-freakin'-hoo.
He knows.

35:21.380 --> 35:24.209
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

35:24.252 --> 35:34.219
♪♪

35:34.262 --> 35:37.483
He knows I love him.

35:37.526 --> 35:41.487
♪♪

35:41.530 --> 35:44.751
Charlie: Dad.

35:44.794 --> 35:46.927
♪♪

35:46.970 --> 35:49.712
Hey, pal. How you feelin'?

35:49.756 --> 35:53.151
[ Sighs ] Should ask you
the same question.

35:53.194 --> 35:57.198
I'm tough. So are you.

35:57.242 --> 36:04.292
♪♪

36:04.336 --> 36:06.381
Sorry about Mom.

36:06.425 --> 36:12.953
♪♪

36:12.996 --> 36:15.956
Yeah.

36:15.999 --> 36:17.697
Me, too.

36:17.740 --> 36:21.091
What are we gonna do?

36:21.135 --> 36:22.919
[ Sighs ]

36:22.963 --> 36:25.487
We're gonna get through it.

36:25.531 --> 36:30.231
♪♪

36:30.275 --> 36:32.146
Together.

36:32.190 --> 36:38.283
♪♪

36:38.326 --> 36:40.241
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:40.285 --> 36:42.200
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

36:44.114 --> 36:45.464
[ Gloves snap ]

36:45.507 --> 36:47.509
I hear the surgery
went well.

36:47.553 --> 36:48.945
Hmm.

36:48.989 --> 36:51.078
She'll be dining on nails
in no time.

36:54.168 --> 36:55.778
Look,
why didn't you call me?

36:55.822 --> 36:59.478
Medicine is not just
a science, son. It's an art.

36:59.521 --> 37:01.697
It's about collaboration.

37:01.741 --> 37:04.265
We collaborate
with our patients,

37:04.309 --> 37:06.615
the same way we collaborate
with each other.

37:06.659 --> 37:08.704
I get it.
I didn't listen to you.

37:08.748 --> 37:11.620
No, you didn't hear me.

37:11.664 --> 37:13.187
It's different.

37:13.231 --> 37:15.320
You know, I've been doing this
for a long time.

37:15.363 --> 37:17.409
I know the percentages
as well as you do,

37:17.452 --> 37:20.934
and I knew that that woman
didn't need surgery right away.

37:20.977 --> 37:22.327
That's not it.

37:22.370 --> 37:24.590
Campbell's been teaching me
to own my decisions,

37:24.633 --> 37:27.288
to be more assertive,
like him.

37:27.332 --> 37:29.116
[ Chuckles ]

37:29.159 --> 37:32.554
Son, if your goal is to become
Will Campbell, good luck.

37:32.598 --> 37:34.295
[ Scoffs ] Thanks.

37:34.339 --> 37:35.688
'Cause that's never
gonna happen.

37:35.731 --> 37:40.083
But if your goal is
to become a great doctor,

37:40.127 --> 37:42.912
you have got to blaze
your own trail.

37:42.956 --> 37:45.915
Remember who you are,
young squire.

37:45.959 --> 37:47.700
It's the only way
you're going to become

37:47.743 --> 37:50.659
who you're truly meant
to be.

37:50.703 --> 37:54.054
♪♪

37:54.097 --> 37:56.665
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

37:56.709 --> 37:59.059
Almost there. Ooh!

37:59.102 --> 38:01.627
Ooh. What you got?
What you...

38:01.670 --> 38:02.845
Go fish.

38:02.889 --> 38:04.891
You just hustling me,
huh, buddy?

38:04.934 --> 38:07.110
They come by it honestly.

38:07.154 --> 38:09.156
-Mommy!
-Hey, Mom.

38:09.199 --> 38:10.984
Go ahead.

38:11.027 --> 38:12.768
[ Chuckles ]

38:14.379 --> 38:16.642
I missed you so much.

38:19.209 --> 38:22.691
You know, I should've been here.
I should've been here.

38:22.735 --> 38:24.780
I was just...

38:24.824 --> 38:27.783
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

38:27.827 --> 38:29.481
You can do this.

38:29.524 --> 38:31.396
[ Sniffles ]

38:32.745 --> 38:36.226
Okay.

38:36.270 --> 38:39.534
[ Exhales sharply,
clears throat ]

38:39.578 --> 38:47.629
You guys deserve
the best mommy in the world.

38:47.673 --> 38:51.329
And right now...

38:51.372 --> 38:53.940
I'm just not her.

38:53.983 --> 38:56.334
What happened
to you guys...

38:58.771 --> 39:01.034
It was my fault.

39:03.384 --> 39:04.733
[ Sighs ]

39:04.777 --> 39:08.520
And I am so sorry.

39:08.563 --> 39:12.480
♪♪

39:12.524 --> 39:14.395
[ Weakly ] Do we
get to go home with you?

39:14.439 --> 39:23.361
♪♪

39:23.404 --> 39:25.406
I've spoken
to your mommy's case worker,

39:25.450 --> 39:30.150
and if she's willing
to get treatment...

39:30.193 --> 39:31.760
♪♪

39:31.804 --> 39:35.895
...then yes.
You do get to go home with her.

39:35.938 --> 39:39.464
[ Sniffles ]

39:39.507 --> 39:43.163
♪♪

39:43.206 --> 39:45.295
You know I love you so much.

39:45.339 --> 39:47.385
Sliders for the lady.[ Siren wailing in distance ]

39:47.428 --> 39:49.343
[ Sighs ] Wow.

39:49.387 --> 39:50.649
Whole day stuck
in your office,

39:50.692 --> 39:52.999
and now you're buying me
dinner from a truck?

39:53.042 --> 39:57.786
Mm. I heard you weren't actually
in my office all day.

39:57.830 --> 40:01.094
Andyou were
in center stage.

40:01.137 --> 40:03.792
[ Helicopter blades whirring
in distance ]

40:03.836 --> 40:05.664
I heard you were a big help
with Max.

40:05.707 --> 40:08.928
Is...he okay?

40:08.971 --> 40:11.191
Yes,
thanks to you and Ariel.

40:11.234 --> 40:14.324
I just went to get help.
[ Chuckles ]

40:14.368 --> 40:16.675
I'm glad you were there.

40:16.718 --> 40:18.416
Proud of you.

40:18.459 --> 40:25.379
♪♪

40:25.423 --> 40:27.381
Mom! [ Laughs ]

40:27.425 --> 40:30.776
-Oh! I missed you.
-How are you?

40:30.819 --> 40:33.343
-I am so good.
-[ Chuckles ]

40:33.387 --> 40:35.128
♪♪

40:35.171 --> 40:38.348
-Look at you.
-[ Gasps ]

40:38.392 --> 40:40.350
♪♪

40:40.394 --> 40:42.396
Thank you, Will.

40:43.789 --> 40:48.141
It's just, um,
eat your food.

40:48.184 --> 40:50.578
Thank you, Daddy.

40:50.622 --> 40:55.844
So what's for dinner? [ Laughs ]

40:55.888 --> 40:57.759
Sweetie?

40:57.803 --> 40:59.500
[ Indistinct conversations ]

40:59.544 --> 41:02.416
Time to go home.Can we have, like,
five more minutes, please?

41:02.460 --> 41:07.552
Okay.
I'll be waiting over here.

41:07.595 --> 41:09.423
[ Indistinct conversations ]

41:09.467 --> 41:11.686
Oh, hi.

41:11.730 --> 41:13.340
We were just
about to leave.

41:13.383 --> 41:15.037
Um...

41:15.081 --> 41:18.345
I think we got off
on the wrong foot.

41:18.388 --> 41:20.129
I'm sorry.

41:22.523 --> 41:24.177
They like each other.

41:24.220 --> 41:26.048
[ Sighs ]

41:26.092 --> 41:29.399
♪♪

41:29.443 --> 41:31.489
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

41:31.532 --> 41:34.927
[ Radio chatter ]

41:34.970 --> 41:37.930
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

41:37.973 --> 41:40.106
[ Radio chatter continues ]

41:40.149 --> 41:43.370
♪♪

41:43.413 --> 41:45.459
Ethan. [ Breathing heavily ]

41:45.503 --> 41:48.941
Tell me something hopeful.
Please. Anything.

41:48.984 --> 41:52.118
That poem
that your brother wrote.

41:52.161 --> 41:56.949
Will you tell me that?
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:56.992 --> 41:58.733
♪♪

41:58.777 --> 42:00.996
-What are you staring at?
-Huh?

42:01.040 --> 42:03.695
-What are you staring at?
-Nothing.

42:03.738 --> 42:07.786
Nothing?I was just wondering
how they're doing,

42:07.829 --> 42:10.440
Larssen and his son.
-They're talking.

42:10.484 --> 42:12.486
Who knows how long
it'll last?

42:12.530 --> 42:14.401
Apple fell pretty
far from the tree.

42:14.444 --> 42:16.446
But it still came
from the tree.

42:16.490 --> 42:19.406
Who are we talkin'
about now?

42:19.449 --> 42:21.321
Freud.

42:21.364 --> 42:25.412
[ Siren wailing in distance ][ Chuckles ]

42:25.455 --> 42:30.243
[ Motor revving ]

42:30.286 --> 42:40.209
♪♪

42:40.253 --> 42:45.040
♪♪

42:55.660 --> 43:05.626
♪♪

43:05.670 --> 43:07.628
♪♪
